  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;NHS website not accurate as to treatment available&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Claire&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended at around 10.15pm on Friday 3 January 2020 for an ankle sprain as per the advice given on the NHS website to attend an urgent care centre (rather than A&amp;amp;E) for a sprain - this hospital was listed as my closest. Reception were very pleasant and helpful and booked me in quickly, informing me that an X-ray wouldn't be possible at the hospital (as A&amp;amp;E department wasn't open) but someone could have a look and send me elsewhere if they felt an X-ray was necessary - this was fine, as the whole point in going was that I wasn't sure if an X-ray would be needed and to get advice. However, the triage nurse informed me that they would not in fact look at minor injuries at all and that I should attend an A&amp;amp;E department instead. She didn't seem interested when I queried this and mentioned that it went completely against what was advised on their own website, only saying 'oh, a few people have mentioned that'! There was no apology for the incorrect information. So the whole thing was a completely wasted trip, which was a bit frustrating, particularly as the department wasn't at all busy when I was there. If the nurse was correct in what she told me, the NHS website should not be directing people to this urgent care centre for this type of issue!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
